gomodel:SYNGO_732  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Tpd52 is present in FASS-sorted, VGluT1Venus-containing synaptosomes.\n\nSubcellular fractionation revealed Tpd52 to be strongly enriched in the synaptic cytosol fraction (LS2, Fig.6H). Immunocytochemistry of cultured hippocampal neurons revealed colocalization with VGluT1, PSD-95 and MAP2 immunoreactivity (Fig.6J,K and S4).\n\nAntibody: Tpd52 (1:250; Shehata et al, 2008): Membranes were washed twice with TBS and incubated with affinity-purified rabbit polyclonal D52 antisera (1:100). No specific information on the antibody or the specificity.. Experimental description: Briefly, forebrains of one or two mice were homogenized..." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" ;
        dc:date           "2017-08-17" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_732" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

